<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910308-0034</DOCNO><DOCID>910308-0034.</DOCID><HL>   Senate Panel Approves   Nominee for Drug Post</HL><DATE>03/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4</SO><GV>CONGRESS (CNG)</GV><LP>   WASHINGTON -- The Senate Judiciary Committee approved thenomination of former Florida Gov. Bob Martinez to become theso-called White House drug czar.   The vote was 11-3, with three Democratic senators, EdwardKennedy of Massachusetts, Howard Metzenbaum of Ohio and PaulSimon of Illinois dissenting. The full Senate is expected toconfirm the Martinez appointment soon.</LP><TEXT>   Republicans praised the nominee for stiffening prisonsentences and building more prisons in Florida. The threedissenting Democrats charged that by imprisoning moredrug-possession defendants, the Martinez administration hadforced the early release of many violent felons. Sen. Simonsaid he opposed the nomination because Mr. Martinez refusedto forswear any partisan political activity while he holdsthe drug policy job.   Committee Chairman Joseph Biden (D., Del.), who generallytries to mediate partisan disputes on the frequentlycontentious panel, said he supported the nomination but thathe had reservations about Mr. Martinez's qualifications.</TEXT></DOC>